1. Install Required Software (If not already installed)
Tool	Download
Python (3.10+)	https://www.python.org/downloads/windows/

Git for Windows	https://git-scm.com/download/win

While installing Python â†’ Check the box âœ… "Add Python to PATH".

2. Clone Your GitHub Repository

Open Command Prompt (cmd) or PowerShell:

git clone https://github.com/sarika0607/GulmohurFashion.git
cd GulmohurFashion

python -m venv venv

venv\Scripts\activate

pip install -r requirements.txt

5. Place Firebase Key Safely (Very Important)

DO NOT put the .json key inside your project.

Instead create a folder outside the project, safe on your system:

mkdir C:\keys


Move your Firebase key file into it:

C:\keys\gulmohur-service-account.json

6. Create .env File in Project App Folder

Navigate to your app folder (the folder containing app.py):

cd gulmohour_boutique_app


Create .env:

echo FIREBASE_KEY_PATH=C:\keys\gulmohur-service-account.json > .env


Your .env file should now look like:

FIREBASE_KEY_PATH=C:\keys\gulmohur-service-account.json

8. Ensure .env and Keys are Ignored (Not Sent to GitHub)

In your top-level .gitignore, these must be present:

.env
venv/
*.json


If .json is not there â†’ Add it.

ðŸ’¡ Quick Summary (Windows Version)
